        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
              
              
          
            
                
                  <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5afead0c506fbe072ef6c2f7/1526826725272-SAIH3J5MJLF4WI8MYTRK/image-asset.jpeg" data-image-dimensions="924x511" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="5b0186e46d2a734d9ccabf17" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5afead0c506fbe072ef6c2f7/1526826725272-SAIH3J5MJLF4WI8MYTRK/image-asset.jpeg?format=1000w" />
                
            
          
        
            
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p>In this example I am mixing together two Subsurface shaders, a Diffuse shader, and a GGX Gloss shader. To get a red scattering lobe, I am overlaying the color inputs of the SSS shaders with two complimentary colors, slightly weighted towards red, and I am using two different scattering radiuses to simulate two skin layers. For the specular component I am remapping the fresnel node to allow individual control over the F0 and F1 parameters.&nbsp;</p>



































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
              
              
          
            
                
                  <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5afead0c506fbe072ef6c2f7/1526826768100-58LRIC6QA3S3J701SOB3/image-asset.jpeg" data-image-dimensions="1682x869" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="5b01870faa4a99a865dd0b9b" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5afead0c506fbe072ef6c2f7/1526826768100-58LRIC6QA3S3J701SOB3/image-asset.jpeg?format=1000w" />
                
            
          
        
            
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  

































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
