  <p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1526825853364_1688"> Here is the second edition of my Zbrush Practical Material Set that I’ve created a few years ago. I thought of sharing it here since the original post is buried deep on the ZBrush Central forums.</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1526825853364_1691">Today I mostly use the real time shaders from the set since they respond to light direction changes and they are a bit more versatile.</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1526825853364_1694">Copy the files into the ZStartup\Materials Directory and restart ZBrush</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1526825853364_1697">Download: <a href="https://static1.squarespace.com/static/5afead0c506fbe072ef6c2f7/t/5afead6f124f1c1116b47ba3/1481884242633/Undoz_ZbrushParticalMatSet.rar">Undoz_ZbrushParticalMatSet.rar</a></p>]]></description></item></channel></rss>